
3-6 easy lines, C++, Java, Python, Ruby

https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-duplicates-from-sorted-array-ii/discuss/27976

* Lang:    cpp
* Author:  StefanPochmann
* Votes:   683

Same simple solution written in several languages. Just go through the numbers and include those in the result that haven't been included twice already.

**C++**

    int removeDuplicates(vector<int>& nums) {
        int i = 0;
        for (int n : nums)
            if (i < 2 || n > nums[i-2])
                nums[i++] = n;
        return i;
    }

**Java**

    public int removeDuplicates(int[] nums) {
        int i = 0;
        for (int n : nums)
            if (i < 2 || n > nums[i-2])
                nums[i++] = n;
        return i;
    }

**Python**

    def removeDuplicates(self, nums):
        i = 0
        for n in nums:
            if i < 2 or n > nums[i-2]:
                nums[i] = n
                i += 1
        return i

**Ruby**

    def remove_duplicates(nums)
        i = 0
        nums.each { |n| nums[(i+=1)-1] = n if i < 2 || n > nums[i-2] }
        i
    end
